<h2>Compatibility with browsers and assistive technology</h2>
<p>
  This site is designed to be compatible with the greatest range of assistive
  technologies. The following environments are tested as part of the development
  process:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Safari + VoiceOver (MacOS)</li>
  <li>Safari + VoiceOver (iOS)</li>
  <li>Chrome + VoiceOver (MacOS)</li>
  <li>Windows + NVDA</li>
  <li>Safari + Voice Control (MacOS)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Technical specifications</h3>
<p>
  The accessibility of this site relies on the following technologies to work
  with the particular combination of web browser and any assistive technologies
  or plugins installed on your computer:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>HTML</li>
  <li>WAI-ARIA</li>
  <li>CSS</li>
</ul>
<p>
  These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility
  standards used.
</p>

